  "doc_id": "39349",
  "text": "Hepatic hemangioma phenotype in the HOXB7-Cre driven Vhlh knockout mice HOXB7-Cre is widely used to target the collecting ducts of the kidney [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, we recently found that this Cre driver is also expressed in a subset of distal tubules in the kidney cortex. Conditional inactivation of Vhlh using this Cre driver resulted in fully penetrant hyperplasia, cysts, clear-cell lesions, inflammation and fibrosis in the kidney, with the hyperplastic lesions arising primarily from Tamm-Horsfall positive distal tubules [CITATION_3] .",
